	<section>
		<article class="container">

			<div class="row">
				<div class="grid-two-thirds float-center">


					<h1 id="get-started">Getting Started</h1>


					<h2 class="text-left">1. Include Buoy on your site.</h2>

		            <pre><code class="language-markup">&lt;script src="buoy.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>

		            <p>Make sure Buoy is included before any scripts that make use of it.</p>


		            <h2 class="text-left">2. Use Buoy's functions in your scripts.</h2>

		            <p class="space-bottom-small"><code>hasClass( element, class )</code> - Check if an element has a class.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">var turkey = document.querySelector('#turkey');
if ( buoy.hasClass(turkey, 'sandwich') ) {
    // Do stuff...
}</code></pre>

		            <p class="space-bottom-small"><code>addClass( element, class )</code> - Add a class to an element.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">var turkey = document.querySelector('#turkey');
buoy.addClass(turkey, 'sandwich');</code></pre>

		            <p class="space-bottom-small"><code>removeClass( element, class )</code> - Remove a class from an element.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">var turkey = document.querySelector('#turkey');
buoy.removeClass(turkey, 'sandwich');</code></pre>

		            <p class="space-bottom-small"><code>toggleClass( element, class )</code>  - Add or remove a class from an element.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">var turkey = document.querySelector('#turkey');
buoy.toggleClass(turkey, 'sandwich');</code></pre>

		            <p class="space-bottom-small"><code>getSiblings( element )</code> - Get an array of siblings for an element.</p>
<pre><code class="language-javascript">var turkey = document.querySelector('#turkey');
var turkeyFriends = buoy.getSiblings(turkey);
[].forEach.call(turkeyFriends, function (friends) {
    // Do stuff...
});</code></pre>


		            <h2 class="text-left">3. Pat yourself on the back.</h2>

		            <p>Seriously, you're done. Nice work! Modify as needed.</p>

		            <p>New to vanilla JS? Check out <a href="http://gomakethings.com/ditching-jquery-for-vanilla-js/">Ditching jQuery for Vanilla JS</a>.

					<hr>

				</div>
			</div>

